Press Releases.Title: 2 New Cases of Locally Transmitted  Covid-19 Infection
Press Releases.MainContent:
As of 20 October 2020, 12pm, the Ministry of Health (MOH) has preliminarily confirmed 2 new cases of locally transmitted COVID-19 infection. Based on our investigations so far, both reside in dormitories and there are no new cases in the community.  

2.      In addition, there are 4 imported cases, who had all been placed on Stay-Home Notice upon arrival in Singapore. In total, there are 6 new cases of COVID-19 infection in Singapore today. 

3.      We are still working through the details of the cases, and further updates will be shared via the MOH press release that will be issued tonight. 


MINISTRY OF HEALTH
20 OCTOBER 2020
